The patch replaces unsafe scanf calls with bounded format specifiers (e.g., "%49[^
]s", "%19s", "%76[^
]s") to enforce maximum input lengths. This directly mitigates out-of-bounds writes caused by unchecked user input, which is the essence of CWE-787. The changes are confined to a few functions and files, making the fix localized and coherent.

